Basic Parameters

Default Settings

Contract Start Date: Automatically set to 10 years before the last available actual LMP data for your selected ISO/Zone.

Contract Term: Defaults to 120 months (10 years) ending at the last available actual LMP month.

LMP Projection: For future months beyond available data, the tool uses a rolling average of historical LMP values (1-5 years) from the same month in prior years.

Cost Calculation Formula (Simplified)

Fixed Cost: Fixed All-In Price Usage

Index Cost: [(Non-Energy Costs) + (LMP + 5%) Open % + (Block Rate + 5%) Hedged %] Usage

Where Non-Energy Costs = Capacity + Transmission + Ancillary Services

LMP Projection: For months beyond available data, uses the selected rolling average method (1-5 years) to forecast LMP values based on historical patterns.

Hedge Strategy Configuration
Quick Apply Settings
Hedge Percentage 50%

How It Works

Simple hedging applies the same fixed block rate and percentage across your entire contract. The calculation includes 5% line loss added to both the LMP and fixed block rate. Your blended energy cost = ((LMP + 5%) Open %) + ((Block Rate + 5%) Hedged %)

Advanced Matrix Configuration

Create custom hedging strategies by setting different fixed block rates and percentages for each month. This allows you to hedge more during high-price seasons and less during low-price periods. All rates automatically include 5% line loss in the calculation.

Dynamic LMP Adjustment
LMP Adjustment Factor +0.0%

Real-time adjustment: Move the slider to instantly see how LMP changes affect your analysis (-100% to +100% in 0.5% increments). The red line shows the break-even point where fixed becomes cheaper than index.
